The paper deals with algorithms for finding maximum matchings in geometric intersection graphs, which are graphs whose vertices correspond to geometric objects in the plane and edges correspond to intersections between these objects. This falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS, cs.GT) sub-categories. The paper also uses algebraic methods to compute the rank of a matrix, which falls under discrete mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses reductions of the maximum matching problem in certain geometric intersection graphs to the case of bounded density, which falls under complexity theory (cs.CC) sub-category.
